Hadn't been here in while, and the Wife wanted the Corn and Crab Soup or whatever it was. I was indifferent as it's more expensive hat I like to pay, but thought why not. They had stuff on the menu for our kids, they had the Chicken Tenders with a side of Mac and Cheese and overall it was a good experience. We didn't wait long, the food was good, all parties were satisfied. So because of this good experience we went back again not 2 weeks later and I wish we hadn't. First off the wait was an hour, so we almost didn't bother (wish we hadn't), but they did have a booth by the bar, so we snatched it up. We didn't expect the royal treatment service-wise as we were sat at the bar, and we got exactly that, the bare minimum of attention. But that wasn't the issue on this visit, on this visit the first issue came when kids kids started screaming that their mouths and throat were on fire. They tend to overreact so we told them to just have a drink, but they kept it up and sure enough they were justified. The Chicken Tenders were loaded with spice. This certainly wasn't the case last time. The waitress said they toss the tenders in buffalo seasoning (really?). Last time they were fine and this time you toss ALL your chicken in buffalo spice? She said they could remake the chicken without the spice but it may take a while. It did. Their food didn't come back out until we all almost done. My Wife's usual Corn and Crab (I wanna say Bisque?) came out and it was missing something... It was missing most of the corn and the crab! You know what it wasn't missing? SPICE! She was going to complain, but was also very hungry and because our waitress was waitressing the 1% we doubt we'd see her for a while. On to my food, while it wasn't terrible, it was not as nice as the previous visit. Once again though the heavy handed spice merchant reared it's head as my burger was extra spicy this time. We reluctantly paid for our food and boxed up the kids chicken and left knowing full well we wouldn't not be back for a while.
